==Translingual==

===Alternative forms===
* In mainland China (based on {{w|GB 18030}} encoding standard), Japanese {{w|kanji}} and Vietnamese [[Nôm]], the left component is {{l|mul|答}}.
* In Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macau (based on {{w|Big5}} encoding standard), the bottom component is {{l|mul|㓣}}, which is the orthodox form found in the {{w|Kangxi dictionary}}. Note that this form is identical with that of {{l|mul|箚}} (<code>U+7B9A</code>).
* Due to {{w|Han unification}}, this character will appear differently depending on the font used.

